Geography & Climate of Pangara

Overall Climate: Predominantly warm to hot. Heavy magical influence causes unusually fertile soil in many regions.
Major Biomes:
Great Golden Savannahs (central) — Endless grasslands, home of the Golden Pride.
Emerald Jungles (south) — Dense, humid rainforests ruled by Serpentis.
High Thunder Peaks (east) — Sky Talons territory.
Bloodplains (eastern border) — Corrupted, blood-red grasslands scarred by demonic wars.
Iron Highlands (north) — Rugged, mineral-rich hills of the Ironhides.

Major Threats: Massive monster migrations, internal clan wars, demonic incursions on the eastern borders, and aggressive megafauna (dire beasts, thunder lizards, etc.).


Economic Reality
Beastkin economies are tribal, volatile, and war-oriented. Despite their high population, they remain relatively poor compared to humans or dwarves due to:

Constant internal conflicts and raids between confederations.
Heavy losses from demonic wars on the eastern borders.
Lack of large-scale infrastructure and lost Golden Age technology.
Nomadic/semi-nomadic lifestyles in many territories.

Main Trades & Exports:

Mercenary services (the biggest export — Beastkin warriors are highly sought after by human kingdoms).
Exotic hides, ivory, bones, and monster materials.
Rare herbs, spices, poisons (especially from Serpentis).
Feathers, sky-metals, and high-quality leather armor.
Slave raiding (unfortunately common).

Overall Condition:

Golden Pride, Ironhides, and Serpentis are the most stable and powerful.
Bloodplains Horde and Deepfang Tribes live in a near-permanent war economy.
Most Beastkin live as hunter-gatherers, raiders, or seasonal farmers. Wealth is measured in strong warriors, healthy herds, and totemic artifacts rather than gold.

The Beastkin are the most populous mortal race after humans, yet their fragmentation prevents them from becoming the dominant power on Aetheria. Many believe that if the Blood Moon Calling ever returns and truly unites them, the balance of the world would shift dramatically.
